We have [a KB that is referenced a lot in support issues|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/How+to+Clear+Confluence+Plugins+Cache] that really could be invalidated by forcing Confluence to rebuild the contents of the plugin-related directories on each startup.  We have seen issues persist through restarts that this method will fix, and if a restart could provide the same solution, it would save customers a lot of pain.

Ideally this functionality could also be made available through the front end, so an admin can clear the plugin cache without a restart of the instance.

